<p>Brains generally process dead tissue via direct necrosis<sup class="footnoteref"><a id="footnoteref-630985-1" href="javascript:;" class="footnoteref" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.utils.scrollToReference('footnote-630985-1')">1</a></sup> whereas scarring is abnormal - cutting it out might make it happen more. Maybe they could be manipulated into them projecting their brains into an unaltered<sup class="footnoteref"><a id="footnoteref-630985-2" href="javascript:;" class="footnoteref" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.utils.scrollToReference('footnote-630985-2')">2</a></sup> state?</p>
<div class="footnotes-footer">
