					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/psul" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2156983); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=2156983&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610204570" alt="psul" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=2156983)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/psul" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2156983); return false;" >psul</a></span> <span class="odate time_1482145467 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">19 Dec 2016 11:04</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2711960">
									

<p>Interesting your thought about clinical tone. Changing this draft from SCP to PL format was an exercise in changing the tone - it retains a lot of the quasi-scientific language, but the PL format encourages the use of marketing-speak and corporate euphemisms. My personal favourite is &quot;the terms of their employment has leaked to the market. As a result, future recruitment efforts are expected to be heavily contested&#8230;&quot;.</p>
<p>I know that PL isn't meant to be the &quot;capitalism is evil&quot; GOI, but I like the idea of their enthusiasm for the science leading them to take shortcuts on the ethics. <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/grant-request-for-genetically-engineering-low-cost-organic-a">This PL format article</a> was definitely an influence on me in that respect.</p>

							</div>

								
					
